The OpenTelemetry OTLP wire format and proto schema are defined by the
OpenTelemetry project:

  opentelemetry-proto — https://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry-proto
                       (Apache-2.0)

The Swift implementation is original; no upstream source is included or
generated. Field numbers and message structures are encoded by hand against
the proto schema.

This product depends on:

  swift-bytes         (https://github.com/bare-swift/swift-bytes,
                        Apache-2.0 with LLVM exception)
  swift-varint        (https://github.com/bare-swift/swift-varint,
                        Apache-2.0 with LLVM exception)
  swift-otlp-exporter (https://github.com/bare-swift/swift-otlp-exporter,
                        Apache-2.0 with LLVM exception)

The proto-encoding internals (ProtoWriter, per-message Common encoders) are
intentionally duplicated from swift-otlp-exporter; this package extends the
same OTLP namespace with trace-specific types and re-uses the public common
types (Resource, InstrumentationScope, KeyValue, AnyValue).
